org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.camera

Class CameraProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core.Provider<T,S>
      • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core.AndroidProvider<VoidData,ImageData>
        • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.camera.CameraProvider

  • public class CameraProvider
extends AndroidProvider<VoidData,ImageData>
    Basic provider for taking photos using CameraAPI v1. Only one photo should be taken at a time for the same request (id).
    Author:
    Riccardo Mancini
    See Also:
    https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/media/camera

      • takePicture

        private void takePicture(long requestID)
        Takes a picture (non-blocking). It also saves the orientation of the phone when the photo was taken. It publishes a progress of 0 as the start of the request.
        Parameters:
        requestID - the id of the request the taken photo belongs to.
        See Also:
        Camera.takePicture(Camera.ShutterCallback, Camera.PictureCallback, Camera.PictureCallback)
